pr-worktree-rm

Pick git worktrees in the current repo via fzf and delete them. The
current worktree and the main/primary worktree are excluded from the
picker.

Each row shows:

  <path>  <branch>  <merge-status>  <pr-status>

where merge-status is "merged" if the branch tip is an ancestor of
origin/main, otherwise "unmerged" (squash-merged PRs typically show
"unmerged" here — rely on pr-status to know they're actually landed),
and pr-status is one of  open#N | closed#N | merged#N | no-pr.

TAB toggles multi-select; ENTER asks for confirmation before deleting.
Worktrees that fail a normal removal are retried with --force, and
`git worktree prune` is run at the end.

Requires: gh, git, fzf, jq.
